Huawei’s new MateBook X Pro is coming to South Africa. The MateBook X Pro, which Huawei calls “a thing of beauty”, features a 3K resolution touchscreen and runs on Windows 10. Huawei told MyBroadband the laptop will arrive in South Africa towards the middle of 2018. Local pricing for MateBook X Pro is yet to be finalised, but recommended prices, at this stage, should be between R23,999 and R29,999. Huawei unveiled the MateBook X Pro at Mobile World Congress 2018, detailing three models: The devices are powered by a battery which promises 12 hours of battery life, while the MateBook X Pro also features several connectivity options – including a USB-A, two USB-C, and headphone jack ports. The MateBook X Pro will be available in Space Grey and Mystic Silver.